How to run the game and our code:
By following these steps, you can run the project with different configurations directly from the terminal.
1.	Navigate to the Project Directory
2.	For playing the game run the file Game.py (use ARROWS to move, R to change piece and SPACE to place.)
Python Game.py
Available Options:
• --display: Set to True for a graphical UI, or False for running without a display (default is True).
• --format: Specify the format of the game. Available options are:
•	play (default)
•	DFS (Depth First Search)
•	A_star (A* algorithm)
•	agent (runs the game with an AI agent)
•	--agent: If using the agent format, choose an AI agent: NextMoveMaximizer Agent, AlphaBetaAgent, or ExpectimaxAgent (default is AlphaBetaAgent).
•	--depth: Set the depth for searching the game tree (default is 1).
•	--sleep_between_actions: Specify whether to pause between actions (default is False).
•	--score_goal: Set the score goal for the DFS and A* formats (default is 10000).

For example:
1.	To run the game using Depth First Search (DFS) with a score goal of 5000:
python Game.py --format DFS --score_goal 5000 --display True
2.	To run the game using A* search with a score goal of 10000 without GUI:
python Game.py --format A_star --display False
3.	To run the game using the AlphaBetaAgent with a depth of 1:
python Game.py --format agent --agent AlphaBetaAgent --depth 1 --display True
